fix: harden hardcoded assumptions found in the longevity audit

Swept src + ingests for values that rot as time/data move (follow-up to the
Q1-vs-Q2 chart find). Fixed the ones that lose data or mislead:

- ingest-digital-marketing: raise read-range ceiling 1500 -> 5000 rows. It's
  the one section-anchored, single-tab ingest (cannot auto-discover like the
  others), so rows past the window were silently skipped as year-sections stack.
  Needs an Edge Function redeploy to take effect.
- Genericize hardcoded "2026" in UI source labels (KpiStrip, MoMChart,
  TopRealtors, PlotSizePivot, DigitalMarketingPanel, RealtorManagement empty
  state) so captions don't read "2026 LAND" when viewing other years.
- Clean stale INGEST_2026_START_ROW / row-676 comments in parseMediaWeeklyTab
  (media now reads the whole per-year tab; no row offsets remain).

Documented the remaining low-risk hardcoding in HANDOVER B9.1 (fixed read-range
caps on marketing-expense/realtor-managers, DEFAULT_PRESET='h1' landing view,
NON_REP_TABS exclusion list, EARLIEST_DATA_YEAR fallback). PROGRESS updated.

